RACE.RACE_TEXT: LONE STAR PARK RACE 1 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 85. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 34500. (PLUS UP TO $6,900 Open ATB) FOR FILLIES THREE YEARS OLD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES OR CLAIMING PRICE $55,000. Weight, 122 lbs. Claiming Price $55,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: APPROPRIATED FUNDS settled off the early pace along the fence, angled out at the quarter pole to mount a convincing rally and pull away late in the drive in a well handled ride. IT TAKES HEART broke alertly to duel for the lead from between horses, took command turning for home, was no match for the winner but finished gamely to be clearly second best in a good effort. FOOLISH DELIGHT reserved near the back of the pack in the early going, commenced a rally at the three-eighths pole, and closed well in a long steady drive. JENNY'S PENNY stalked the lead from three wide, made a bid at through the turn and flattened out in the drive. SHE'S JERSEY TUFF raced prominently four wide to the turn and faded. MOR PEANUTS rushed up to an early lead, dueled from the rail through the turn and gave way. SWEET SLEW trailed and was never a factor.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LONE STAR PARK RACE 2 6F Dirt CR: 84. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 34500. (PLUS UP TO $6,900 Open ATB) FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, OR TEXAS BRED ALLOWANCE OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES OR CLAIMING PRICE $30,000. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since January 23, 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since October 23, 2022 Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $30,000 (Maiden Or Claiming Races Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: STACI'S RED DRESS was off slowly at the start, then was well rated along the inside into the turn, shifted out to the four path in the early stretch, dug in gamely, and showed up in the late stretch just in time to prove best. FASHION RAGE chased the pace while two wide, bid from the three path on turn, gained the lead from the dueling pair mid stretch, continued to menace gamely but was out finished in the end by an outer foe and was second best. BENDELENE chased the pace along the inside into the turn, angled out four wide in the early stretch to rally and was closing well in the end. RECLUSIVE tracked the pace while two wide then bid while four wide throughout the turn, came in slightly and brushed rival, re bid and continued to close well in the late stretch. REDEFINITION lead the way to the top of the turn, then was confronted by an outer rival entering the lane, continued to hold a strong bid down the late stretch but was out bid in the end by outer rivals. WENDY'S SONG stalked the pace while three off the rail, was moving up throughout the turn to duel with the pace setter heading into the stretch, continued to bid mildly then gave way in the end. OUTLINING tracked the pace from the inside, was moving up while four wide on the turn to bid in the upper stretch, but was brushed by an outer rival and had no final bid in the end.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LONE STAR PARK RACE 3 1M Dirt CR: 63. Maiden Claiming Purse 15000. (PLUS UP TO $750 Open ATB) FOR TEXAS ACCREDITED MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $15,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: RED DRAW took command entering the first turn, repelled the pace pressers in the far turn and gamely held the closers safe in the late going. JOHN LOUIS' BEVO well rated off the pace early, rallied four wide in the turn to loom up, dropped back at the top of the lane and came on again late in the drive splitting horses to gain the place. LOST GOLD raced prominently in striking position throughout and finished willingly while unable to reel in the winner. EAGLEFORD raced five wide into the first turn, settled off the pace, was put to a drive entering the far turn and rallied well to be gaining late. ASTA LAVISTA HONEY broke outward into rivals path leaving the gate, settled into a pressing position down the backside, challenged at the quarter pole and flattened out in the stretch. LITTLE JOHN HENRY reserved off the leaders while racing behind a wall of runners down the backside and failed to respond when called upon for the drive. WITT SWEET SIXTEEN trailed early, threw his head about leaving the first turn when encountering kickback, made a brief bid in the far turn and tossed head again turning for home and drifted out when gaining on the field.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: RED SUMMERBIRD tracked the pace two off the rail, came out three wide to bid on the turn, dug in gamely and surged past the pace setter in the late stretch and was up at the wire. TAPITURE JONES moved quickly along the inside to gain the lead around the five eighths pole and into the turn, was in a hard drive to edge clear in the upper stretch and kept on till the deep stretch but was out finished just at the wire. I'M A COWBOY chased the pace along the inside into the turn, rallied well to vie for the lead in the early stretch then gave way in the end. MY LITTLE PRINCE was away well to gain the short lead, then was over taken by an inner rival, continued to press the pace heading into the turn, was in a hard drive to try to gain the lead again but was extinguished and flattened out in the end. ZAVALA was in a hard drive to stalk the pace while three wide, was used up on the turn and flattened out in the lane. POSEIDONS WAVE trailed behind the field and was no factor.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: SKYKAT rated in mid-pack for the run down the backside, lacked racing room into the far turn, angled out three wide when clear and prevailed in a hard drive. FOR FUN tracked the pace from the fence, rallied gamely along the rail in the lane to be closing fast late to just miss in a good effort. MALIBU MIDNIGHT shuffled to the rear of the field down the backside, circled wide and closed full of run. CATO'S LADY stalked the pace at the front of the pack chasing the run off leader, rallied into the turn to be close up turning for home and was outkicked by the closers. KRINKLES was prominently placed while forced to race wide throughout, made a bid in the far turn and flattened out in the drive. MY GOLDEN BLING raced off to open a wide lead down the backside in rapid fractions and stopped in the lane. PAINTBRUSH flashed speed for a half mile and came up empty.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: WICKED SONG dueled on the lead from the rail, responded to all challenges, persistent in the drive and cleared late in a game effort. RACE.FOOTNOTES: REBEL POSSE bid for the lead along the inside into the turn then menaced in the upper stretch and surged to the wire to be up just in time. MY PAL MATTIE lead the way along the inside, cleared the turn, continued to menace gamely in the stretch but was caught at the wire and was second best. SHANNON C was in a hard drive to press the pace while three wide into the turn, continued to rally well down the lane then gave way in deep stretch. SIMPLY WICKED raced in the middle of the field while four wide, then bid on the turn came out six wide in the stretch to rally but it was too little too late. CHATTALOT raced in the two path behind most of the field, made a mild bid on the turn and into the stretch and was no threat.
